adults, since very poor literacy and numeracy levels are present amongst 16-to-25-year-olds in the United 
Kingdom and the United States. 3 Across the OECD area, countries where the "tail" in the distribution of 
skills among the adult population is largest also tend to experience higher poverty rates in a point in time 
